## 2. PostgreSQL (with pgvector)

- Public (via cloudflared access tcp): `pg.${ROOT_DOMAIN}:5432`
- Local on the WSL/Linux/macOS host: `localhost:5432`
- From inside k8s: `postgres.infra-bridges.svc.cluster.local:5432`
- User: `${POSTGRES_USER}`
- Password: `${POSTGRES_PASSWORD}`
- Default DB: `${POSTGRES_DB}`
- Enabled extensions: `vector`, `uuid-ossp`, `pg_trgm`

### Connection strings

```
# From a k8s app
postgresql://${POSTGRES_USER}:${POSTGRES_PASSWORD}@postgres.infra-bridges.svc.cluster.local:5432/${POSTGRES_DB}

# From the host (WSL/Linux/macOS) directly
postgresql://${POSTGRES_USER}:${POSTGRES_PASSWORD}@localhost:5432/${POSTGRES_DB}

# From a remote dev workstation, after `cloudflared access tcp ...`:
postgresql://${POSTGRES_USER}:${POSTGRES_PASSWORD}@localhost:5432/${POSTGRES_DB}
```

DBeaver / DataGrip — see `i18n/en/docs/04-client-access.md`.

