## 6. ArgoCD

- Web UI: `https://argocd.${ROOT_DOMAIN}`
- User: `admin`
- Initial password (or fetch via the command below):
  ```bash
  kubectl -n argocd get secret argocd-initial-admin-secret \
    -o jsonpath='{.data.password}' | base64 -d
  ```
  Also written to `.env` as `ARGOCD_ADMIN_PASSWORD`.
- Recommended: change the password after first login (`argocd account update-password`).
- Manifest repo: `${MANIFEST_REPO_URL}` (branch `${MANIFEST_REPO_BRANCH}`)

## 7. Tekton CI (webhook + pipeline + dashboard)

- Webhook URL: `https://hooks.${ROOT_DOMAIN}`
- Webhook secret: `${GIT_WEBHOOK_SECRET}` (Tekton EventListener verifies this on every push)
- Dashboard UI: `https://tekton.${ROOT_DOMAIN}` (PipelineRun / TaskRun / log viewer; can cancel runs, delete runs from the UI)
  - **BasicAuth user:** `${OUTPOST_DASHBOARD_USER}`
  - **BasicAuth password:** `${OUTPOST_DASHBOARD_PASSWORD}`
  - Hardening: replace BasicAuth with Cloudflare Access (Zero Trust) at the edge — gate by email OTP / IdP. The middleware can stay enabled as defense in depth.
- Active git provider plugin: `${GIT_PROVIDER_PLUGIN}`
- Configure your repos to send Push events to the URL above with the secret.

Pipeline behaviour:

```
1. push   →  EventListener  →  PipelineRun
2. git-clone        clone the app repo at the pushed commit
3. kaniko-build     build a Docker image
4. push-image       push to <REGISTRY_HOST>/<repo>:<short-sha>
5. update-manifest  patch image tag in the manifest repo, commit, push
6. ArgoCD sync      → kubectl apply → rolling deploy
```

Inspect runs:

```bash
kubectl get pipelinerun -n tekton-pipelines
kubectl logs -n tekton-pipelines -l tekton.dev/pipelineRun=<run-name> \
  --all-containers --tail=200
```

