## 11. Test gate, auto-rollback, notifications

Full design: `i18n/en/docs/proposals/cicd-test-gate.md`. Walkthrough in
`i18n/en/docs/00-quickstart.md` Phase J.

### Active plugins

- Test runner: `${TEST_RUNNER}` (mode: `${TESTKUBE_MODE}`)
- Rollout plugin: `${ROLLOUT_PLUGIN}`
- Notification providers: `${NOTIFICATION_PROVIDERS}`

### Endpoints

- Argo Rollouts Dashboard: `https://${ROLLOUTS_DASHBOARD_HOST}` — canary progress, abort, promote
  - **BasicAuth user:** `${OUTPOST_DASHBOARD_USER}` / **password:** `${OUTPOST_DASHBOARD_PASSWORD}` (shared with Tekton Dashboard — same Traefik middleware)
- Testkube agent: namespace `testkube` (`kubectl get pods -n testkube`)
- Argo Rollouts controller: namespace `argo-rollouts`

### Notification fan-out

Every PipelineRun failure / ArgoCD sync failure / Argo Rollouts auto-rollback
fans out to all enabled notification providers. Configure / disable channels
by editing `NOTIFICATION_PROVIDERS` in `.env` (comma-separated) and re-running
`bash bootstrap.sh`.

| Provider          | Webhook URL var          | Sign secret var (optional)   |
|-------------------|--------------------------|------------------------------|
| dingtalk          | `DINGTALK_WEBHOOK_URL`   | `DINGTALK_SIGN_SECRET`       |
| feishu            | `FEISHU_WEBHOOK_URL`     | `FEISHU_SIGN_SECRET`         |
| wecom             | `WECOM_WEBHOOK_URL`      | (none — protect URL itself)  |
| webhook-generic   | `GENERIC_WEBHOOK_URL`    | `GENERIC_WEBHOOK_BEARER`     |

### Test contract (per application repo)

Drop `outpost.test.yaml` at the repo root:

```yaml
version: 1
runner:
  command: ["sh", "-c", "go test ./..."]   # or pytest, npm test, mvn test, dotnet test
gates:
  pre-deploy:        { timeout: 5m }
  post-deploy-smoke: { enabled: true, image: curlimages/curl:8.10.0,
                       command: ["sh","-c","curl -fsS http://my-app.apps.svc.cluster.local/healthz"],
                       timeout: 30s }
```

Repos without `outpost.test.yaml` (and without `Dockerfile.test`) skip Gate A
cleanly — pipeline still runs.

### Auto-rollback thresholds (locked)

Default `AnalysisTemplate`: `failureLimit: 2`, `consecutiveErrorLimit: 3`,
`successCondition: result == "Passed"` (Job provider) or `result == 200`
(Web HTTP probe).

## 12. Hardening checklist (recommended, not enforced)

- [ ] Add Cloudflare Access (email OTP) in front of `argocd.${ROOT_DOMAIN}`, `mq.${ROOT_DOMAIN}`, `tekton.${ROOT_DOMAIN}`, `${ROLLOUTS_DASHBOARD_HOST}` — replaces / supplements BasicAuth at the edge.
- [ ] Rotate `OUTPOST_DASHBOARD_PASSWORD` (set blank in `.env`, re-run `bash bootstrap.sh`).
- [ ] Add basic auth or Cloudflare Access in front of `registry.${ROOT_DOMAIN}` if exposing publicly (currently anonymous).
- [ ] Change ArgoCD admin password (`argocd account update-password`).
- [ ] Backup `secrets-backup/sealed-secrets-pub.pem` to a password manager.

## 13. Reuse checklist (when onboarding a new project)

See `i18n/en/docs/05-onboard-project.md`. In short:

1. Create a Gitee/GitHub/GitLab repo with a `Dockerfile`
2. Add `apps/<name>/{deployment,service,ingress}.yaml` to the manifest repo
3. Add `argocd-apps/<name>.yaml` to the manifest repo
4. In the application repo, configure a webhook → `https://hooks.${ROOT_DOMAIN}` with secret `${GIT_WEBHOOK_SECRET}`
5. `git push origin main` and watch ArgoCD synchronise

Connection strings come from §0 of this file.
